d cultural nuances in tales that are at once earthy and whimsical and that also parallel stories found in the larger Arab folk tradition. Featuring a new foreword by Ibtisam Barakat, Speak, Bird, Speak Again is an essential text in Palestinian culture and a must for those who want to deepen their understanding of an enduring people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aFolk literature, ArabiczPalestinevTranslations into English. 0aPalestinian ArabsvFolklore. 0aTaleszPalestine. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Folklore & Mythology.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aarab.  aarabs.  abridegrooms.  abrides.  acourtship.  acreation myths.  aenvironment.  afairy tales.  afiction.  afolk narrative.  afolklore.  afolktales.  agalilee.  agaza.  agender.  ahusbands and wives.  aislam.  alove.  amiddle east literature.  amiddle east.  amotif index.  amythology.  anature.  anonfiction.  aoral tradition.  apalestine.  apalestinian arab.  apalestinian culture.  apalestinian folktales.  apalestinian studies.  aparenting.  aromance.  asexuality.  asocial science.  astorytelling.  atypology.  awest bank.1 aBarakat, Ibtisam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDundes, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanaana, Sharif, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520385856zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520385856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520385856/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP